	Good location comfortable room great value	The Silverton is a great place to headquarter for touring Las Vegas and area sights. Close to the strip with excellent interstate access, the facility carries the Bass Pro Shop theme into the resort. The rooms are tastefully decorated, quite comfortable, and plush. There is little noise and the rooms are fresh. For us nonsmokers it is a nice retreat from the casino. The casino itself is a lot of fun and has several restaurants, with a beautiful saltwater aquarium at the entrance. We have stayed here three times and will return for its ambiance and good value for Vegas.	
