Sep 4 2008 	Excellent Stay But?	I just finished a stay at the Silverton Casino. I have been to vegas to many times to count and decided a stay at Silverton would be a nice change. Valet can be a bit slow depending on the day and events that are in the area. Self Park was very convient if you decided to go that route. A super target and all the other stores that follow are just across the street. The front desk staff was very nice and helpful. We were able to check in at 900am with no problem. At check in we were given some very good coupons from booking through expedia. You will need a rental car at this location. The decor was rustic and had a disney wilderness lodge theme which was very cool. The pool was one that you would find at a community center. It is very plain, but peaceful. The room was very nice, the beds were the most comfortable bed that we have ever slept on in vegas, The ac worked great. The bathroom is the problem, it is very very small. There is no room for two peolple. It is nice just small. The bed bath and beyond soaps and lotions were a nice touch. Mi Casa is a mexican rest. at the resort, it is great, ask what the special for the day is. We saved 50% by ordering this way. The buffet was excellent, our expedia coupons allowed both of us to eat crab legs for $9.00 total. They were great and even better at $9.00. Our las night we ate at Twin Creeks Steak house. This place was EXCELLENT, it will cost you around 120.00 four a couple, but it was worth it. The Bass Pro Shop is attached to this resort so you can go price your favarite rifle and then play Blackjack to earn the money to buy it. I will never stay anywhere but Silverton Casino. The following are negatives that we encountered from other locations this trip.NYNY has massive construction going on inside, jack hammers were so loud you could not here delaers talking to you.Tony Romas Steak and Lobster at Fitzgeralds was a joke, the lobster was good but the steak was like eatting shoe leather.T