Aug 18 2008 	Not perfect but a pleasure to stay at!	I am just finishing up my 4 night stay at the Silverton. I haven been very impressed overall. Rooms: the rooms are nice and comfortable. They are not fancy, but they are clean. The t.v. is a 27&quot;, and also is nothing fancy but it gets the job done. The rooms are clean, and the beds are pretty comfortable. Not as comfortable as at home, but they get the job done. Although I couldn't get the wireless internet to work, they had a network cable plug in, and the network connection was very fast.Casino: The casino like the rooms, is nothing fabulous, but it gets the job done. It is nicely laid out and has a lot of different options. Table games are plentiful, though it is very possible you will be the only person playing. I was playing double deck $5 blackjack and it was just me! The poker room is pretty bad. I was only actually able to play 1 time as there was never enough people to play. There is a lot of choices and the casino was not overly smoky in my opinion unlike some other posters said. Hotel Services: The valet was a tad lacking. They were never very busy, but it took quite a bit of time (15 minutes) on average to get the car. It also took some time to drop off your car because sometimes there were no valet employees around. Still much quicker to get your car than at a mega resort because there aren't 100 people in front of you, and the workers worked hard, just seemed to be a little understaffed. Room service was average, nothing great, but the price was good. It was very iffy at night whether or not you would be able to get food. One night when I called at 1:00 a.m., nobody answered so I called the front desk. They said &quot;Oh they must not be at their post call them back in 5 minutes&quot;. So 5 minutes, then 10 minutes, then 15 minutes later i called, and was never able to gety anything. Business services were non existent, and if you want a boarding pass printed you have to have the front desk do it since they don't have a business center.Dining: We only ate at the buffet and room service. Buffet was very good, especially the sunday brunch. We were very impressed, and for $16.99 you got a very good buffet with unlimited champagne drinks like mimosa's. The dinner buffer was $19.99 and with it you got unlimited house wine. As I said earlier room service was good, if unspectacular. Good value for the money.Location: I really liked the location. It's very convenient to I-15. If you are not going to rent a car though, DO NOT STAY HERE. I always get a rental in Vegas, and have no idea why you wouldn't get one. If you don't I would not stay here. Would probably be at least a $15 cab ride to the MGM one way, if you could get one. I never saw one out front. They have a shuttle, but it only goes every 5 hours??? I don't know why they bother, every 5 hours? They're only 10 or 15 minutes from the MGM, so why they couldn't go every 1 or 2 hours, I don't know. I think it boils down to the running theme of the hotel, which is that they are a tad understaffed. Overall: I really like this hotel. I know I mentioned a lot of negative things about this hotel, but I would definitely stay here again. I paid $40 a night including tax, and for that price I wouldn't stay anywhere else. It has a few problems, but the rooms are clean, the employees friendly and the food is good. I also really like the location, but make sure you get a rental car. I stayed at the Venetian and Signature MGM Grand my las two times to Vegas. This place obviously isn't as nice. But for the money, it definitely is great. My wife and I are coming back to Vegas in February, and this will be where we stay.	
