nd ended up enjoying our three night stay! We would definitely come back here on our next Vegas trip and give this hotel/casino another try!	
Nov 18 2006 	Excellent Value	We stayed at the Silverton 11/13 - 11/16. Our rate was $50 per night. Check-in took about 4 minutes. Our room was on the ground floor, but didn't smell smokey at all. The room was very quiet, clean and up to date. The TV, AC, blow dryer, etc. worked great. The beds were a little on the firm side, which was good for us. They provided plenty of towels, although they might want to throw in a little fabric softener once in awhile. We ate breakfast twice in the cafe and it was okay. Overall, this is a great value, easy to get in and out of, easy access to the strip (if you have a car). This is not a party hotel, but was just what we needed to come back to after a busy day/night at the strip. My only concern would be that with the exception of a couple of bartenders at the casino bars and a very young clerk at check-out, the staff wasn't very friendly. They weren't rude necessarily, but acted like they were just going through the motions and didn't really care if we were there or not. Other than that our stay was great.	
